                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "comments": {
                "nodes": [
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c5yHpro",
                    "body": "style nit:\r\n```suggestion\r\n- `Matrix.schur_triangulation` : a matrix `A : Matrix n n ð` with `ð` being algebraically closed can\r\n  be decomposed as `A = U * T * star U` where `U` is unitary and `T` is upper triangular.\r\n- `Matrix.schurTriangulationUnitary` : the unitary matrix `U` as previously stated.\r\n- `Matrix.schurTriangulation` : the upper triangular matrix `T` as previously stated.\r\n- Some auxilary definitions are not meant to be used directly, but\r\n  `LinearMap.SchurTriangulationAux.of` contains the main algorithm for the triangulation procedure.\r\n```",
                    "createdAt": "2025-01-14T10:42:35Z",
                    "author": {
                      "login": "eric-wieser"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
