                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOFcwZ1c5yJeVr",
                    "body": "`Fin.subNat` takes a `Fin (n + m)` while `Fin.subNat'`\r\n1. takes a `Fin (m + n)`,\r\n2. makes `m` implicit, and\r\n3. accepts `Â¬ i < m` instead of `m â¤ i`.\r\n\r\nI intend `Fin.subNat'` to be a placeholder for `Sigma.snd : Fin n` when `Î£ b, cond b (Fin m) (Fin n)` has `Sigma.fst = false`. The placeholder just so happened to have a type similar to `Fin.subNat`, so I named it `Fin.subNat'`.",
                    "createdAt": "2025-01-14T15:44:25Z",
